stand and Calculate the Net Present Value, Internal Rate of Return, and Payback Period for Capital Budgeting</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0rem 0px 2px; list-style: disc;\">Calculate the Future Value and Present Value of cash flows Theory?</li>\r\n</ul>', '<h5 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.2; font-size: 24px; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 5px; color: #4f5052; font-family: \'segoe UI\'; background-color: #ffffff;\">Requirements</h5>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 18px; list-style: none; color: #4f5052; font-family: \'segoe UI\'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #ffffff;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0rem 0px 2px; list-style: disc;\">A Raspberry Pi 2 or 3, model B</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0rem 0px 2px; list-style: disc;\">A Windows, Mac, or Linux computer</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding: 0px; margin: 0rem 0px 2px; list-style: disc;\">Understand the difference between fixed and variable interest rates</li>\r\n</ul>', 550, 'courses_26_1676270697download (4).png', 'Proficient', 'Dutch', 8, 24, '2022-09-05 12:11:09'),
